pmmd.notes:
APG3 adds Thomandersiaceae and Linderniaceae as new families;
2 families deleted from the 2005 version based on APG3: Myoporaceae (now in Scrophulariaceae) and Trapellaceae (now in Plantaginaceae);
Stevens' APweb includes more detail in his text than in the tree he shows, including the following: 
Carlemanniaceae sister to Oleaceae; (Calceolariaceae, Gesneriaceae) as a resolved clade;
relationships from Plantaginaceae to (Thomandersiaceae, Verbenaceae) mostly resolved;
resolution below family level pruned
